  "signal_description": "The query retrieves the following information from the 'defaultview-124' table: 'PO Release Cycle Time Range', 'No. of Cases', 'Total PO Amount (INR)', and 'Avg. Cycle Time'. The 'PO Release Cycle Time Range' column is calculated based on the 'CYCLE_TIME' column. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is less than or equal to 3 days, the range is set to '0 - 3 Days'. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than 3 days and less than 5 days, the range is set to '4 Days'. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 5 days and less than 11 days, the range is set to '5 - 10 Days'. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 11 days and less than 16 days, the range is set to '11 - 15 Days'. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 16 days and less than 21 days, the range is set to '16 - 20 Days'. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 21 days and less than 31 days, the range is set to '21 - 30 Days'. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 31 days, the range is set to 'More than 30 Days'. If none of the conditions are met, the range is set to 'Others'. The 'Sequence No' column is calculated based on the 'CYCLE_TIME' column. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is less than or equal to 3 days, the sequence number is set to 0. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 3 days and less than 5 days, the sequence number is set to 1. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 5 days and less than 11 days, the sequence number is set to 2. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 11 days and less than 16 days, the sequence number is set to 3. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 16 days and less than 21 days, the sequence number is set to 4. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 21 days and less than 31 days, the sequence number is set to 5. If the 'CYCLE_TIME' is greater than or equal to 31 days, the sequence number is set to 6. If none of the conditions are met, the sequence number is set to 7. The 'No. of Cases' column is the count of distinct 'Case Id' values. The 'Total PO Amount (INR)' column is the sum of 'PO Item Value' values. The 'Avg. Cycle Time' column is the average of 'Total Cycle Time' values. The results are grouped by the 'PO Release Cycle Time Range' and 'Sequence No' columns and ordered by the 'No. of Cases' column."
